CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper April 27, 1957, pg. A3, reads: "YWCA Open House also brought Dr. Norman Rice, dean of the College of Fine Arts, Carnegie Tech., and director of the Pittsburgh Plan for Art, to the reception to view some of the magnificent paintings loaned to the 'Y' by the PPA. He and Mrs. William J. McKee, chairman of the Downtown YWCA, look at one of the paintings. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Carnegie Tech Dean of Fine Arts Dr. Norman Rice and Mrs. William J. McKee looking at painting of house with label on frame inscribed "...Pittsburgh Plan for Art...,"in Downtown YWCA
